15 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Implementation -- reporting requirement. (1) If the waiver request
16 submitted under [section 4] is approved, the department shall implement the restriction within 6 months after
17 receiving federal authorization.
18 (2) If the waiver request is denied, the department shall resubmit the request annually until
19 approval is granted.
20 (3) The department shall submit an annual report to the governor and the children, families, health,
21 and human services interim committee in accordance with 5-11-210 by September 30 detailing:
22 (a) the status of the waiver request;
23 (b) data on supplemental nutrition assistance program spending patterns in the state; and
24 (c) any identified challenges or recommendations for further policy action.
